00:37:16,864 --> 00:37:21,446
you've just entertained an audience of one and that's it. Like, you haven't done anything.

659
00:37:22,406 --> 00:37:27,589
You've got to think about the performance the whole time. So I try to write as little lore as possible

660
00:37:28,589 --> 00:37:29,110
all the time.

661
00:37:29,657 --> 00:37:35,098
but be thinking about the way that scenes will play or what will actually happen in the game.

662
00:37:35,218 --> 00:37:38,799
And then when I realize I don't know something, then I go back to the lore and I kind of

663
00:37:38,959 --> 00:37:42,239
construct the lore that makes sense within that. And then I go back to the gameplay.

664
00:37:42,439 --> 00:37:47,480
And flip-flopping between those two, you eventually reach a point where both are satisfied.

